Below is a **clean, copy-paste–ready prompt** you can use directly in **Blackbox AI** to generate **Utsav Zone** using **HTML, CSS, and JavaScript**.
This prompt is structured so Blackbox understands **features, UI, and constraints** clearly and does not over-engineer.

---

### Blackbox Prompt (HTML / CSS / JavaScript)

> Build a **responsive festival discovery web app called “Utsav Zone”** using **pure HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript** (no frameworks).
>
> **Core idea:**
> Utsav Zone helps users discover nearby festival pandals/events (starting with Durga Puja), view crowd status, routes, and important details.
>
> **Pages / Sections required:**
>
> 1. **Landing Page**
>
>    * App name: *Utsav Zone*
>    * Tagline: *Discover festivals smarter*
>    * “Explore Pandals” button
> 2. **Explore Page**
>
>    * List of pandals in **card layout**
>    * Each card shows:
>
>      * Pandal name
>      * Area/location
>      * Crowd status badge (Low / Medium / High)
>      * Short description
>    * Search bar to filter pandals by name or area
> 3. **Pandal Detail Modal / Page**
>
>    * Full description
>    * Crowd level indicator
>    * Best visiting time
>    * Route hint (text-based, no maps API)
>
> **UI / Design requirements:**
>
> * Minimal, modern UI
> * Festival-inspired accent colors (red, gold, white)
> * Mobile-first responsive design
> * Smooth hover effects on cards
> * Clean typography
>
> **Technical constraints:**
>
> * No external libraries or frameworks
> * No backend
> * Use **dummy JSON data** inside JavaScript for pandals
> * Code should be **well-commented**
>
> **Optional enhancements (if possible):**
>
> * Crowd status color coding
> * Simple dark/light mode toggle
> * Smooth fade or slide animations using CSS
>
> Output **three separate files**:
>
> * `index.html`
> * `style.css`
> * `script.js`
>
> Keep the code beginner-friendly, structured, and scalable for future features like booking or live crowd updates.

---

### Why this prompt works

* Clear scope (no Flutter, no backend confusion)
* Matches **Utsav Zone’s actual vision**
* Prevents Blackbox from using React or random libraries
* Scalable for future versions (V2, V3)

If you want:

* a **more advanced prompt (map logic, crowd simulation)**
* a **school-project-safe prompt**
* or a **production-grade version**

tell me **which level** and I’ll refine it.
